I stand before you today as a humble individual, prepared to accept full responsibility for my actions. I must admit, with a heavy heart, that I am pleading guilty to the charge of assault.

The events that led to this regretful incident unfolded in a moment of intense frustration and anger. My employee had unfortunately made a grave error that would have significant financial repercussions for my company. The weight of the situation weighed heavily on my shoulders, and in a moment of weakness, I allowed my emotions to get the best of me.

