I am here today to plead guilty and accept full responsibility for the charge of assault. I deeply regret my actions and the harm that I caused to my employee.

In a moment of intense anger, I pushed my employee to the ground and kicked him in the stomach. This was in response to a serious mistake he made at work, which I believed would have significant financial consequences for my company. However, I now understand that my response was completely unacceptable and I should have handled the situation differently.

Immediately after the incident, I took my employee to the closest emergency room to ensure his well-being. I deeply regret the physical harm I caused him, and I understand the distress that this incident has undoubtedly caused both him and his family.

I want to apologize once more to the victim and his family for my actions. I am 40 years old and have no criminal record. I have always strived to make positive contributions to my community and conduct myself with integrity.

I am fully aware of the seriousness of my actions and the impact they have had on the victim and his family. I take full responsibility for my behavior and have learned from this experience. I assure you that I am committed to addressing and improving my anger management issues to ensure that such an incident will never occur again in the future.

